  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance to the Most Vulnerable and Severely Affected Host Communities for Resilience Building and Livelihoods Restoration</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at strengthening and enhancing the disaster risk reduction capacities, social cohesion and livelihoods of host communities in Cox&apos;s Bazar District in Bangladesh. It includes measures to prevent or mitigate disaster risks through resilience measures combined with the strengthening of preparedness mechanisms for the benefit of both refugee and host communities. The project will adopt an inclusive participatory approach to ensure that the needs, capacities and voices of the most vulnerable segments of society, including women, youth and displaced populations, are integrated in planning and programme activities throughout implementation.</narrative>
  </description>
